SEIVER stalked the pace from the inside throughout the first three quarters, was in a long drive leaving the turn, dug in gamely while brushing an outer foe in the early stretch then pulled away from the battling foes to finish second best. ANIMAL PRINCESS lead the way into the first turn to set the pace down the backstretch, was under a easy hand ride before dueling with an outer rival at the top of the far turn, lost command but continued to menace gamely down the stretch to share the show prize in the end. BOARDWALK FRIES was well rated while two wide down the backstretch and throughout the far bend, then rallied at the top of the stretch to close willingly in the end. CONSTITUTIONALRAGE moved down the backstretch from the inside in the middle of the field, then bid between rivals on the far turn to menace from the four path in the early stretch, was brushed slightly, then continued to close gamely in the end. QIA was rank early then settled back behind the field, was moving up on the far turn, came out five wide and found more in the stretch to close well but it wasn't enough. MY JO JO settled along the inside throughout the first half then gained speed quickly on the far turn to challenge for the lead but it wasn't enough and gave way in the final furlong. COLETTE'S SPIRIT settled at the back of the field while two wide on the backstretch, then rallied on the far turn and into the stretch but came up empty. GRASS CUTTER was out four wide heading into the backstretch, then was moving up swiftly to duel for the lead while two wide, was hard used after the half and dropped back and had no final bid. PER RULING FROM THE HORSERACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, ANIMAL PRINCESS HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.
